tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, and a slightly decreased total CO₂, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Renal function and electrolytes are normal. Recommend clinical correlation and consideration of diabetes management optimization.
